The contradiction lies between Evidence 4 (Lake Photo) and Testimony 0 (Lotta's statement). 

Lotta states that she clearly saw Mr. Edgeworth on the boat ("I saw it clear as day. The man on the boat was Mr. Edgeworth!"). However, Evidence 4 is a photo taken at the time of the incident which shows two persons shooting at each other, but "the fog is so dense that neither of the men's faces can be seen clearly." So, Lotta's testimony claiming clear identification of Mr. Edgeworth contradicts the visual evidence that the faces cannot be seen clearly due to the fog.

